<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880115-0160 </DOCNO><HL> Philadelphia Stock Exchange </HL><SO> </SO><IN> MON SCR </IN><DATELINE> PHILADELPHIA  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Philadelphia Stock Exchange said trading in foreign currency options rose 30% to a record 10.5 million contracts in 1987.    In 1986, the currency-options volume was 7.9 million contracts. Since December 1982, more than 23.3 million of the contracts have been traded at the exchange. </TEXT></DOC>